# Response
I cannot give you a "yes" or "no" because this is a decision about your safety, your values, and your future that only you can make.

However, I can tell you this: The answer is "No" if you are only doing it because the wedding is this Saturday.

In a healthy relationship, the discovery of a planned act of mass violence is not "just a story"—it is a life-altering revelation. If you say "yes" today without resolving the deep knot in your stomach, you aren't saying yes to a marriage; you are saying yes to a lifetime of wondering who she really is when she’s pushed "into the pond."

You should only go through with the wedding if:

The Secret is Gone: You feel she has been 100% transparent about why she kept this from you and what else might be hidden.

The Change is Real: You are certain she has processed that darkness through professional help, not just "grown out of it."

The Peace is Back: You can look at her at the altar and feel the same safety and love you felt a week ago.

If you feel dread, confusion, or a need to "fix" her, then the answer for this Saturday is No. You can always get married later, but you can never "un-know" this. Trust your gut. It is currently trying to protect you.

